00056 GHash *BLI_ghash_new(GHashHashFP hashfp, GHashCmpFP cmpfp, const char *info)
00057 {
00058     GHash *gh = MEM_mallocN(sizeof(*gh), info);
00059     gh->hashfp = hashfp;
00060     gh->cmpfp = cmpfp;
00061     gh->entrypool = BLI_mempool_create(sizeof(Entry), 64, 64, 0);
00062 
00063     gh->cursize = 0;
00064     gh->nentries = 0;
00065     gh->nbuckets = hashsizes[gh->cursize];
00066 
00067     gh->buckets = MEM_mallocN(gh->nbuckets * sizeof(*gh->buckets), "buckets");
00068     memset(gh->buckets, 0, gh->nbuckets * sizeof(*gh->buckets));
00069 
00070     return gh;
00071 }

00078 void BLI_ghash_insert(GHash *gh, void *key, void *val)
00079 {
00080     unsigned int hash = gh->hashfp(key) % gh->nbuckets;
00081     Entry *e = (Entry*)BLI_mempool_alloc(gh->entrypool);
00082 
00083     e->key = key;
00084     e->val = val;
00085     e->next = gh->buckets[hash];
00086     gh->buckets[hash] = e;
00087 
00088     if (++gh->nentries > (float)gh->nbuckets / 2) {
00089         Entry **old = gh->buckets;
00090         int i, nold = gh->nbuckets;
00091 
00092         gh->nbuckets = hashsizes[++gh->cursize];
00093         gh->buckets = (Entry**)MEM_mallocN(gh->nbuckets * sizeof(*gh->buckets), "buckets");
00094         memset(gh->buckets, 0, gh->nbuckets * sizeof(*gh->buckets));
00095 
00096         for (i = 0; i < nold; i++) {
00097             for (e = old[i]; e;) {
00098                 Entry *n = e->next;
00099 
00100                 hash = gh->hashfp(e->key) % gh->nbuckets;
00101                 e->next = gh->buckets[hash];
00102                 gh->buckets[hash] = e;
00103 
00104                 e = n;
00105             }
00106         }
00107 
00108         MEM_freeN(old);
00109     }
00110 }

00112 void *BLI_ghash_lookup(GHash *gh, const void *key)
00113 {
00114     if (gh) {
00115         unsigned int hash = gh->hashfp(key) % gh->nbuckets;
00116         Entry *e;
00117 
00118         for (e = gh->buckets[hash]; e; e = e->next)
00119             if (gh->cmpfp(key, e->key) == 0)
00120                 return e->val;
00121     }
00122     return NULL;
00123 }

00170 {

00172 
00173     if (keyfreefp || valfreefp) {
00174         for (i = 0; i < gh->nbuckets; i++) {
00175             Entry *e;

00198 GHashIterator *BLI_ghashIterator_new(GHash *gh)

00269 unsigned int BLI_ghashutil_inthash(const void *ptr)
00270 {
00271     uintptr_t key = (uintptr_t)ptr;
00272 
00273     key += ~(key << 16);
00274     key ^=  (key >>  5);
00275     key +=  (key <<  3);
00276     key ^=  (key >> 13);
00277     key += ~(key <<  9);
00278     key ^=  (key >> 17);
00279 
00280     return (unsigned int)(key & 0xffffffff);
00281 }
